title: Former Oregon prep wrestlers currently competing at NCAA Division 1 colleges
text:
Former Oregon prep wrestlers currently competing at NCAA Division 1 colleges Updated February 21, 2017 Comment FORMER OREGON PREP STARS WRESTLING AT DIVISION 1 SCHOOLS 
Oregon has produced some great wrestling talent, and right now there are plenty of the top guys competing at the NCAA Division I level. This slideshow highlights their accomplishments and sacrifice, and if someone has been left out, email a picture and some info to Billy Gates at bgates@oregonian.com. 
There are also many wrestlers competing at other collegiate levels, NAIA for instance, and we will showcase them down the road. For now, here are the Division I guys. Doug Beghtel 
High schools: Hermiston and Crook County 
Sophomore at Nebraska, one win shy of All-America status during last year's NCAA championships. Nebraska Athletics
